HEADWORD: Gith
<hw>Gith</hw> <pr>(g⟦icr⟧th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E., corn
cockle; cf. W. <ets>gith</ets> corn cockle.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The corn cockle; also anciently applied to the <gen>Nigella</gen>,
or fennel flower.</def>⟦br⟧
